<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/224554-how-does-this-compare-to-meditations-is">How does this compare to Meditations, is it similar to the Meditations in writing where there are statements rather than arguments or the opposite?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_224554'><a id="like_count_community_question_224554" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/224554?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">8 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F97411.Letters_from_a_Stoic">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/224554-how-does-this-compare-to-meditations-is">7 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/224554-how-does-this-compare-to-meditations-is">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
