<div id="review_4043910951" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4043910951" />
    <a title="Gabrielė Bužinskaitė" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/77345457-gabriel-bu-inskait"><img alt="Gabrielė Bužinskaitė" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1629145375p2/77345457.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4043910951?book_show_action=true">Jun 06, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gabrielė Bužinskaitė" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gabrielė Bužinskaitė" href="/user/show/77345457-gabriel-bu-inskait">Gabrielė Bužinskaitė</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780141395852" href="/book/show/22571572-letters-from-a-stoic">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4043910951" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6611475402714546508">“You ask me to say what you should consider it particularly important to avoid. My answer is this: a mass crowd.”<br/><br/>The best book I have ever read on stoicism. I learned so much more of what it takes to be stoic, the values and the reasoning behind it.<br/><br/>In my experience, stoic philosophers’ works tend to be rather difficult to read, but Seneca, thankfully, believes in using plain and simple speech in the pursuit of truth. Reading a book of wisdom written 1956 (!) years ago in uncomplicated and unders</span>
  <span id="freeText6611475402714546508" style="display:none">“You ask me to say what you should consider it particularly important to avoid. My answer is this: a mass crowd.”<br /><br />The best book I have ever read on stoicism. I learned so much more of what it takes to be stoic, the values and the reasoning behind it.<br /><br />In my experience, stoic philosophers’ works tend to be rather difficult to read, but Seneca, thankfully, believes in using plain and simple speech in the pursuit of truth. Reading a book of wisdom written 1956 (!) years ago in uncomplicated and understandable language feels like nothing but a blessing to me.<br /><br />After reading Letters from a Stoic I have great admiration not only for Seneca’s work, but also for him as a person. Although extremely wealthy, he lead a simple, minimalistic and honourable life, and was a genius way ahead of his time. This book, however, is a collection of letters he sent to a young man Lucilius, giving him lessons and tips on how to be a better stoic. The absolute majority of the advices can still be applied today. I couldn’t recommend this book more.<br /><br />“What good does it do you to go overseas, to move from city to city? If you really want to escape the things that harass you, what you’re needing is not to be in a different place but to be a different person.”</span>
  <a data-text-id="6611475402714546508" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


